♪ NOTHING STANDING IN OUR WAY

04:28.093 --> 04:31.009
-SEE, MATT?
I TOLD YOU THIS
WASN'T MY IMAGINATION.

04:32.097 --> 04:33.751
EVER SINCE RUPERT
MANSFIELD'S DEATH,

04:33.882 --> 04:35.884
GUESTS HAVE REPORTED
STRANGE OCCURRENCES

04:36.014 --> 04:37.102
IN THIS ROOM.

04:38.147 --> 04:40.758
SWAYING CURTAINS,
SUDDEN GUSTS OF WIND,

04:40.889 --> 04:42.760
PICTURES FALLING OFF THE WALL.

04:42.891 --> 04:44.980
HOW ARE YOU GONNA
EXPLAIN ALL THESE THINGS?

04:45.807 --> 04:47.112
AND THEN WHAT ABOUT
THE FACE THAT I SAW

04:47.243 --> 04:48.200
IN THE MIRROR?

04:48.331 --> 04:49.637
OR THE PICTURE THAT YOU TOOK

04:49.767 --> 04:51.291
THAT SUDDENLY WENT UP IN FLAMES?

04:52.683 --> 04:54.772
AND NOT TO MENTION THE
FACT THAT DIANA SUTHERLAND

04:54.903 --> 04:56.687
LOOKS LIKE SHE COULD
BE MY TWIN SISTER.

04:58.123 --> 04:59.603
COME ON, MATT,
YOU'RE GONNA TELL ME

04:59.734 --> 05:02.084
THAT NONE OF THIS SEEMS
THE SLIGHTEST BIT UNUSUAL?

05:02.214 --> 05:03.607
-OKAY.

05:03.738 --> 05:05.130
I'LL ADMIT IT'S UNUSUAL, BUT I--

05:05.261 --> 05:07.045
-BUT YOU STILL DON'T
BELIEVE ME, DO YOU?

05:08.308 --> 05:11.659
-SUMMER, THERE'S NO
SUCH THING AS A GHOST.

05:11.789 --> 05:16.881
-[OMINOUS MUSIC]

05:20.102 --> 05:21.582
-OH MY GOD.

05:22.104 --> 05:23.323
-[KNOCKING]

05:24.889 --> 05:25.890
-WHO IS IT?

05:26.500 --> 05:27.501
-STEPHANIE.

05:35.335 --> 05:37.467
I DID SOME CHECKING UP
ON DIANA SUTHERLAND.

05:37.989 --> 05:38.816
GUESS WHAT?

05:39.382 --> 05:40.209
-WHAT?

05:40.340 --> 05:41.515
-SHE'S STILL ALIVE.

05:46.520 --> 05:51.481
-[BIRDS CHIRPING]

06:34.524 --> 06:36.961
-MRS. SUTHERLAND,
YOU HAVE VISITORS.

06:37.092 --> 06:39.224
-HI, I'M MATT BRODY.

06:39.355 --> 06:40.574
THIS IS SUMMER QUINN.

06:41.357 --> 06:42.706
-HOW DO YOU DO?

06:42.837 --> 06:44.404
-HI, IT'S NICE TO MEET YOU.

06:45.492 --> 06:47.189
-YOU'RE A VERY LOVELY GIRL.

06:47.319 --> 06:48.669
-THANK YOU.

06:51.541 --> 06:52.629
-DO I KNOW YOU?

06:52.760 --> 06:53.978
-NO.

06:54.501 --> 06:56.938
SEE, WE'RE GUESTS AT
THE HOTEL DEL CORONADO.

06:58.592 --> 07:00.115
WE CAME OVER TO ASK
YOU A FEW QUESTIONS

07:00.245 --> 07:01.682
IF YOU WOULDN'T MIND.

07:01.812 --> 07:02.770
-I'M SORRY.

07:03.597 --> 07:04.946
I'M REALLY VERY TIRED.

07:07.905 --> 07:09.298
SOME OTHER TIME, PERHAPS.

07:09.907 --> 07:11.692
-I'M AFRAID YOU'LL
HAVE TO GO NOW.

07:12.257 --> 07:15.609
-MRS. SUTHERLAND, SOMETHING
HAS BEEN HAPPENING TO ME,

07:16.218 --> 07:17.480
AND I THINK IT HAS
SOMETHING TO DO

07:17.611 --> 07:18.612
WITH WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU.

07:20.614 --> 07:22.703
IT'S ABOUT RUPERT MANSFIELD.

07:29.710 --> 07:31.276
-NO NO NO NO NO
NO, TAKE IT EASY

07:31.407 --> 07:32.843
JUST TAKE IT EASY.

07:32.974 --> 07:34.410
DON'T EXERT YOURSELF.
YOU JUST STAY CALM.

07:34.541 --> 07:36.107
ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO.

07:36.238 --> 07:37.369
YOU STILL HAVING CHEST PAINS?

07:37.500 --> 07:38.501
-YEAH.

07:38.632 --> 07:39.981
-ALL RIGHT.

07:40.111 --> 07:41.286
JUST LET ME DO ALL
THE WORK HERE, PAL,

07:41.417 --> 07:42.505
YOU JUST TRY AND
GET AS MUCH OXYGEN

07:42.636 --> 07:43.941
INTO YOUR SYSTEM AS POSSIBLE.

07:44.072 --> 07:45.639
ALL RIGHT, THAT'S
GOOD, THAT'S GOOD.

07:45.769 --> 07:46.640
-DAMMIT.

07:46.770 --> 07:47.902
MITCH?

07:48.032 --> 07:49.425
-YEAH?
-HOW ARE WE GONNA GET IN?

07:49.556 --> 07:50.644
-AH, DON'T WORRY.

07:51.862 --> 07:53.081
SOMEBODY'LL SPOT US.

07:53.690 --> 07:56.780
-WHAT IF THEY DON'T? [GROANING]

07:57.477 --> 07:58.695
-I'LL SWIM YOU IN, PAL.

07:59.348 --> 08:00.567
I'LL SWIM YOU IN.

08:00.697 --> 08:02.090
ALL RIGHT, JUST TAKE IT EASY.

08:10.446 --> 08:12.883
-HOBIE: SHOULDN'T
THEY BE BACK BY NOW?

08:13.014 --> 08:14.189
-GET USED IT.

08:15.407 --> 08:17.235
BUZZ NEVER SHOWS UP
WHEN HE'S SUPPOSED TO.

08:23.241 --> 08:24.416
YOU KNOW,

08:25.069 --> 08:26.854
IT'S HARD TO BELIEVE YOUR
DAD AND MY DAD ARE BROTHERS.

08:29.813 --> 08:32.686
I MEAN, THEY'RE LIKE
TOTAL OPPOSITES.

08:33.904 --> 08:35.340
[SIGHING]

08:37.081 --> 08:38.082
WHAT'S IT LIKE
LIVING WITH SOMEBODY

08:38.212 --> 08:39.256
WHO ACTUALLY CARES ABOUT YOU?

08:39.909 --> 08:41.738
-MAYBE YOU'LL COME FIND OUT.

08:42.870 --> 08:43.914
-I DON'T KNOW.

08:45.133 --> 08:46.874
I'M NOT TOO SURE I CAN
HANDLE YOUR OLD MAN, EITHER.

08:52.357 --> 08:54.142
WELL, I DON'T SEE 'EM.

08:56.057 --> 08:56.927
YOU HUNGRY?

08:57.580 --> 08:58.581
-KINDA.

08:58.712 --> 08:59.930
-LET'S GO GRAB A BURGER, DUDE.

09:00.061 --> 09:00.888
-ALL RIGHT.

09:02.890 --> 09:06.981
[PANTING]

09:07.982 --> 09:09.287
-HOW YOU DOIN', BRO?

09:10.071 --> 09:12.813
-I GOT NO FEELING IN
MY ARMS OR MY LEGS.

09:13.683 --> 09:15.206
-I KNOW, I KNOW.

09:15.337 --> 09:16.947
YOU JUST HANG ON, HUH?

09:17.078 --> 09:17.948
HANG ON.

09:19.646 --> 09:21.299
WE'RE ON OUR WAY HOME.

09:35.836 --> 09:37.402
-C.J.: YOU THINK
ROCKY WILL REMEMBER ME?

09:39.404 --> 09:41.015
-DOLPHINS HAVE
EXCELLENT MEMORIES.

09:42.451 --> 09:44.105
-YOU KNOW, EVER SINCE
I WAS A LITTLE GIRL,

09:44.235 --> 09:46.063
I DREAMED OF SWIMMING
WITH DOLPHINS.

09:47.587 --> 09:49.501
I THINK SUBCONSCIOUSLY
THAT'S WHY I BECAME

09:49.632 --> 09:50.590
AN OCEAN LIFEGUARD.

09:52.069 --> 09:54.463
-ACTUALLY, THEY DON'T LET
YOU GET TOO CLOSE IN THE WILD.

09:55.333 --> 09:57.292
-WOMAN: EXCUSE ME, KEITH!
-YEAH?

09:57.422 --> 09:58.902
-WE JUST GOT A REPORT OF A
BEACHED BOTTLE NOSED DOLPHIN

09:59.033 --> 10:00.034
AT CRYSTAL POINT.

10:00.164 --> 10:01.165
-LET'S ROLL!

10:01.296 --> 10:02.558
YOU WANNA COME RESCUE A DOLPHIN?

10:02.689 --> 10:03.515
-ARE YOU SURE I
WON'T GET IN THE WAY?

10:03.646 --> 10:05.213
-COME ON, LET'S GO!

10:13.177 --> 10:14.570
-MAN: HELP'S ON THE WAY!

10:24.449 --> 10:26.669
-KEITH: ALL RIGHT,
BACK UP, PLEASE.

10:29.803 --> 10:30.891
LET'S SEE WHAT WE GOT HERE.

10:32.588 --> 10:33.633
EASY.

10:48.735 --> 10:51.041
-RUPERT AND I HAD
BEEN MADLY IN LOVE.

10:53.174 --> 10:54.871
BUT I WAS MARRIED AT THE TIME,

10:56.003 --> 10:58.919
1AND I KNEW MY HUSBAND WOULD
NEVER GIVE ME A DIVORCE.

11:00.572 --> 11:04.968
RUPERT WAS A VERY SPIRITUAL MAN.

11:06.143 --> 11:10.365
HE BELIEVED THAT OUR
TWO SOULS WERE ONE

11:11.801 --> 11:14.674
AND THAT IF WE COULDN'T
BE TOGETHER IN THIS LIFE,

11:17.677 --> 11:19.548
WE SHOULD GO ON TO THE NEXT ONE.

11:23.334 --> 11:24.858
SO WE MADE A PACT

11:26.642 --> 11:27.991
TO JUMP TOGETHER

11:30.341 --> 11:32.996
FROM THE TOP OF THE
HOTEL DEL CORONADO.

11:48.490 --> 11:53.538
-[OMINOUS MUSIC]

12:03.984 --> 12:06.160
-I KNOW THERE WAS A LOT
OF GOSSIP AT THE TIME.

12:06.290 --> 12:08.858
I WAS ACCUSED OF
MURDERING MY LOVER,

12:09.511 --> 12:10.773
AS WAS MY HUSBAND.

12:14.472 --> 12:16.083
-WHY DID YOU BREAK THE PROMISE?

12:16.692 --> 12:17.649
HOW COME YOU DIDN'T JUMP?

12:20.783 --> 12:22.132
-I BETRAYED HIM.

12:25.527 --> 12:27.964
RUPERT'S LOVE WAS THE ONLY THING

12:28.095 --> 12:30.140
THAT MADE MY LIFE WORTH LIVING.

12:30.271 --> 12:35.319
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

12:50.987 --> 12:52.772
-BUT I COULDN'T DIE FOR HIM.

12:56.210 --> 12:59.039
-OH, I'M SO SORRY TO BRING
BACK ALL THESE MEMORIES.

12:59.169 --> 13:00.780
-OH MY DEAR,

13:01.389 --> 13:03.478
THERE ISN'T A DAY THAT GOES BY

13:03.608 --> 13:04.914
THAT I DON'T THINK OF HIM.

13:06.786 --> 13:08.309
AND THE GUILT THAT I FEEL

13:08.439 --> 13:11.051
FOR LETTING THAT
WONDERFUL YOUNG MAN DIE.

13:14.228 --> 13:16.056
-SO YOU'VE HEARD THE STORIES

13:16.186 --> 13:17.492
THAT HIS SPIRIT LIVES ON.

13:17.622 --> 13:18.972
-OH YES.

13:19.102 --> 13:21.061
-AND THAT RUPERT'S ROOM
AT THE DEL IS HAUNTED.

13:21.670 --> 13:25.500
-YES, BUT I NEVER PUT
MUCH STOCK IN THEM,

13:29.852 --> 13:31.985
UNTIL YOU CAME HERE TODAY.

13:38.774 --> 13:39.949
-WE'RE ON OUR WAY.

13:41.908 --> 13:44.214
MITCH, YOU SEE LAND?

13:44.345 --> 13:45.825
-NO, NOT YET.

13:45.955 --> 13:46.913
-THEN WHY'D YOU STOP?

13:47.043 --> 13:48.392
-I'M EXHAUSTED!

13:50.655 --> 13:53.136
-MITCH, I GOTTA GET BACK, MAN.

13:53.876 --> 13:54.921
I GOT A DATE TONIGHT.

13:55.051 --> 13:56.574
-[LAUGHING]

13:58.141 --> 13:59.534
WHAT ABOUT ME?

14:00.927 --> 14:02.580
-I'LL SEE IF
SHE'S GOT A FRIEND.

14:02.711 --> 14:05.061
-[LAUGHING]

14:05.192 --> 14:06.628
[GRUNTING]

14:17.204 --> 14:18.205
-KEITH!

14:18.335 --> 14:19.249
-HEY!

14:26.387 --> 14:27.431
-HOW IS SHE?

14:27.562 --> 14:29.129
-OH, SHE'S STILL PRETTY WEAK.

14:29.259 --> 14:31.218
WE GAVE HER A
THOROUGH EXAM THOUGH,

14:31.348 --> 14:33.046
SHE DOESN'T SEEM TO HAVE
ANY SERIOUS INJURIES.

14:33.176 --> 14:34.961
-THANK GOD.

14:35.091 --> 14:38.268
-YEAH, BUT IT TURNS OUT
SHE'S RECENTLY GIVEN BIRTH.

14:38.399 --> 14:40.314
WHEN SHE GOT CAUGHT
IN THAT NYLON ROPE

14:40.444 --> 14:42.055
SHE GOT SEPARATED
FROM HER OFFSPRING.

14:42.925 --> 14:44.274
-AND YOU DON'T THINK
SHE'S ROCKY'S MOTHER?

14:44.405 --> 14:46.581
-OH, NO, NO.

14:46.711 --> 14:48.278
BUT THERE'S A CHANCE
THEY MIGHT BOND.

14:48.409 --> 14:50.367
IF THINGS WORK OUT, WE'RE
GONNA PUT 'EM TOGETHER

14:50.498 --> 14:51.934
AND SEE IF WE CAN GET A MATCH.

14:54.632 --> 14:56.069
-YOU HEAR THAT, ROCKY?

14:56.199 --> 14:57.635
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE SOMEONE
TO LOOK AFTER YOU.

15:13.521 --> 15:14.304
STEPHANIE?

15:14.435 --> 15:16.437
-HMM?

15:16.567 --> 15:18.395
-WHAT WOULD YOU SAY
IF I DECIDED TO STAY
HERE IN SAN DIEGO?

15:18.526 --> 15:21.181
-C.J., GIVE ME A BREAK.
YOU CAN'T BE SERIOUS.

15:21.311 --> 15:22.486
-I AM.

15:22.617 --> 15:23.792
I'M THINKING OF MOVING HERE.

15:23.923 --> 15:25.576
-OH, WHAT'S HIS NAME THIS TIME?

15:25.707 --> 15:27.013
KEITH?

15:27.143 --> 15:28.492
-IT'S NOT JUST KEITH.

15:28.623 --> 15:29.972
IT'S EVERYTHING.

15:30.103 --> 15:32.714
IT'S SEA WORLD, THE DOLPHINS.

15:33.933 --> 15:35.586
I JUST FEEL LIKE I FIT IN HERE.

15:36.152 --> 15:37.806
YOU KNOW, MAYBE I
COULD SETTLE DOWN HERE,

15:38.546 --> 15:39.547
START A FAMILY.

15:41.201 --> 15:42.506
-START A FAMILY?

15:43.116 --> 15:45.335
C.J., YOU HAVEN'T EVEN GONE
OUT ON ONE DATE WITH THIS GUY.

15:45.466 --> 15:47.163
-I KNOW, I KNOW.

15:47.294 --> 15:50.427
I ALWAYS CREATE THESE
UNREALISTIC FANTASIES ABOUT MEN

15:50.558 --> 15:52.299
AND THEN WHEN IT DOESN'T
COME TRUE, I'M DISAPPOINTED.

15:53.778 --> 15:55.563
THIS TIME IT'S DIFFERENT.

15:56.520 --> 15:59.175
EVERY TIME I'M WITH
KEITH, IT FEELS SO RIGHT.

15:59.828 --> 16:01.134
WE SHARE THE SAME INTERESTS,

16:01.743 --> 16:03.049
THE SAME VALUES.

16:06.269 --> 16:08.184
HE'S THE FIRST GUY I'VE EVER MET

16:09.229 --> 16:11.840
THAT I CAN ACTUALLY SEE SPENDING
THE REST OF MY LIFE WITH.

16:13.363 --> 16:18.107
-[GENTLE MUSIC]

16:57.625 --> 16:59.540
-STEPHANIE: C.J.,
ARE YOU GONNA ORDER?

17:01.150 --> 17:02.456
-OH, YEAH.

17:02.586 --> 17:03.761
YEAH.

17:05.546 --> 17:07.113
I'M GONNA HAVE THE...

17:07.678 --> 17:09.289
AVOCADO SALAD.

17:09.419 --> 17:10.420
-WOULD YOU LIKE THAT
WITH OUR HOUSE VINAIGRETTE?

17:10.550 --> 17:11.638
-SURE.

17:17.384 --> 17:18.211
HEY!

17:18.340 --> 17:19.342
-HI!

17:19.473 --> 17:21.431
-HI, UH, HAVE YOU SEEN MY DAD?

17:21.561 --> 17:22.563
-NO, WHY?

17:22.693 --> 17:23.564
I THOUGHT YOU GUYS WENT SAILING.

17:24.304 --> 17:25.261
-WE DIDN'T GO.

17:25.392 --> 17:26.262
-AND THEY DIDN'T COME BACK.

17:35.793 --> 17:37.012
-WELL, DO YOU GUYS
KNOW WHERE THEY WENT

17:37.143 --> 17:38.274
OR WHERE THEY WERE SAILING TO?

17:38.405 --> 17:39.319
-THEY DIDN'T SAY.

17:39.449 --> 17:40.668
-WHICH WAY TO NEW ZEALAND?

17:40.798 --> 17:42.539
-LOOK, THEY'RE
PROBABLY BACK BY NOW.

17:42.670 --> 17:44.541
IT TOOK YOU GUYS A WHILE TO
GET HERE FROM THE MARINA.

17:44.672 --> 17:46.021
HAVE YOU CALLED HIM?

17:46.152 --> 17:47.675
-WE LEFT A FORWARD
FOR HIM TO CALL US.

17:49.242 --> 17:50.069
-OKAY.

17:50.199 --> 17:51.026
I UNDERSTAND.

17:51.157 --> 17:52.549
PLEASE KEEP US POSTED.

17:53.550 --> 17:54.377
THANK YOU.

17:57.554 --> 17:58.468
-WAS THAT THE COAST GUARD?

17:59.208 --> 18:00.775
-THEY FOUND BUZZY'S
SAILBOAT DRIFTING

18:00.905 --> 18:02.516
TEN MILES OFF POINT LOMA.

18:04.692 --> 18:05.997
THERE WAS NO ONE ON BOARD.

18:17.748 --> 18:19.228
-[COUGHING]

18:19.359 --> 18:20.316
-THE FARMER SAID,

18:21.187 --> 18:22.623
SAYS TO THE CHINESE SALESMAN

18:22.753 --> 18:24.451
THAT WASN'T A CHICKEN.
THAT WAS MY WIFE.

18:26.322 --> 18:29.586
HERE, OKAY. I GOT ONE.
I GOT ANOTHER ONE.

18:29.717 --> 18:31.458
A MAN GOES INTO A BAR.

18:33.068 --> 18:34.722
A DOG'S PUTTING
MONEY IN THE JUKEBOX.

18:34.852 --> 18:36.071
SO THE BARTENDER SAYS--

18:36.202 --> 18:37.420
[GROANING]

18:37.551 --> 18:39.118
-MITCH, WHAT'S WRONG?

18:39.248 --> 18:40.597
-I GOT A LEG CRAMP.

18:40.728 --> 18:41.816
-LET ME GO, SAVE YOURSELF.

18:41.946 --> 18:42.947
-AH, SHUT UP!

18:43.078 --> 18:44.427
-MITCH...

18:45.776 --> 18:47.604
YOU'RE NOT GONNA MAKE
IT WITH ME. JUST GO ON.

18:47.735 --> 18:48.605
I'M NOT WORTH IT.

18:48.736 --> 18:49.824
-I SAID SHUT UP!

18:49.954 --> 18:51.739
-YOU CAN'T LEAVE
THE BOYS ALONE.

18:51.869 --> 18:53.436
-OH, IT'S UNBELIEVABLE.

18:54.437 --> 18:56.091
ALL OF A SUDDEN, YOU'RE
WORRIED ABOUT KYLE.

18:57.092 --> 18:58.702
YEAH WELL YOU CAN
FORGET IT, PAL.

18:59.616 --> 19:02.619
DYING'S EASY. COMEDY IS HARD.

19:02.750 --> 19:03.968
IT'S YOUR TURN.

19:04.099 --> 19:05.013
LET'S HEAR A JOKE.

19:05.144 --> 19:06.362
[GRUNTING]

19:06.493 --> 19:07.624
DAMMIT!

19:08.538 --> 19:09.409
BUZZY!

19:10.845 --> 19:11.846
BUZZY!

19:11.976 --> 19:13.152
DON'T, BUZZY!

19:13.282 --> 19:14.153
BUZZY!

19:32.345 --> 19:33.607
COME ON! COME ON!

19:33.737 --> 19:34.564
COME ON, MAN!

19:34.695 --> 19:35.826
SPIT IT OUT!

19:35.957 --> 19:36.871
SPIT IT OUT!

19:37.001 --> 19:37.959
BREATHE!

19:38.089 --> 19:39.569
AH, YOU'RE NOT DYIN' ON ME!

19:39.700 --> 19:41.180
YOU'RE NOT DYIN' ON ME!

19:42.920 --> 19:44.095
HANG IN THERE.

19:46.315 --> 19:47.360
COME ON, BREATHE.

19:47.490 --> 19:50.189
THAT'S IT. THAT'S IT. OKAY.

19:50.711 --> 19:51.973
OKAY.

19:55.846 --> 19:57.196
-HOBIE: THEY'VE
GOTTA BE SOMEWHERE.

19:58.719 --> 20:00.286
CAN'T WE DO SOMETHING?

20:01.852 --> 20:03.811
-WELL, WE CAN'T DO ANYTHING
UNTIL IT'S DAYLIGHT, HOBIE.

20:03.941 --> 20:05.682
-WELL, WHY NOT
TAKE OUT THE SCARAB?

20:06.509 --> 20:07.945
-WE WILL AS SOON AS IT'S LIGHT.

20:08.076 --> 20:09.382
BUT UNTIL THEN, WE
JUST HAVE TO SIT TIGHT

20:09.512 --> 20:10.600
AND HOPE FOR THE BEST.

20:13.864 --> 20:14.996
HOBIE.

20:15.910 --> 20:17.346
I KNOW YOU'RE WORRIED,

20:17.477 --> 20:19.218
BUT THE COAST GUARD HAS
MOUNTED A FULL SCALE

20:19.348 --> 20:20.567
SEARCH AND RESCUE OPERATION.

20:23.004 --> 20:24.135
I MEAN THESE ARE THE SAME GUYS

20:24.266 --> 20:25.398
WHO FOUND YOUR DAD
AND ME 200 MILES

20:25.528 --> 20:26.529
OFF THE COAST OF MEXICO.

20:28.618 --> 20:30.185
THIS'LL BE A PIECE
OF CAKE FOR THEM.

20:39.368 --> 20:40.543
-A GUY GOES TO A DENTIST,

20:42.066 --> 20:43.242
SAYS, MY TEETH ARE YELLOW.

20:45.331 --> 20:46.462
WHAT SHOULD I DO?

20:48.551 --> 20:50.118
-WEAR A BROWN TIE.

20:50.249 --> 20:52.468
-[LAUGHING]

20:55.166 --> 20:56.820
-I DON'T UNDERSTAND THIS.

20:57.386 --> 20:59.867
HOW COULD YOU EVEN THINK OF
SETTING FOOT IN THAT ROOM AGAIN?

21:00.389 --> 21:02.261
-MATT, WHAT AM
I SUPPOSED TO DO?

21:02.391 --> 21:03.914
DENY THIS IS ALL HAPPENING?

21:04.480 --> 21:06.265
JUST PRETEND THE WHOLE
THING WAS A DREAM?

21:07.091 --> 21:08.136
CALL GHOSTBUSTERS?

21:08.267 --> 21:09.920
[LAUGHING]

21:10.051 --> 21:12.140
OH MATT, DON'T YOU
SEE WHAT'S HAPPENING?

21:13.315 --> 21:14.534
RUPERT MANSFIELD'S SOUL

21:14.664 --> 21:16.666
HAS REFUSED TO
ACCEPT ITS OWN DEATH.

21:17.406 --> 21:19.713
HE'S REMAINED HERE WAITING
FOR DIANA TO JOIN HIM

21:19.843 --> 21:21.018
IN THE WORLD BEYOND.

21:21.976 --> 21:24.283
MATT, HE THINKS THAT I AM DIANA.

21:25.196 --> 21:26.720
-WELL, HOW DO YOU
KNOW WHAT HE THINKS?

21:26.850 --> 21:29.592
-BECAUSE I CAN
COMMUNICATE WITH HIM, MATT.

21:30.289 --> 21:33.466
I HAVE TO MAKE HIM SEE THAT I
AM NOT THE ONE THAT HE WANTS.

21:34.771 --> 21:37.513
OTHERWISE, HE COULD
BE WITH US FOREVER.

21:40.473 --> 21:42.823
AND YOU THOUGHT IT WAS
TOUGH COMPETING WITH SLADE.

21:42.953 --> 21:44.738
-[LAUGHING]

21:49.525 --> 21:50.613
GOODNIGHT, MATT.

21:51.745 --> 21:52.746
-BYE.

22:03.931 --> 22:07.848
-[OMINOUS MUSIC]

22:13.767 --> 22:15.029
-RUPERT?

22:18.032 --> 22:23.777
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

22:49.411 --> 22:53.284
-C.J., I CAN'T WAIT
AROUND ANYMORE. LET'S GO.

22:53.981 --> 22:54.982
-OKAY.

22:57.811 --> 22:59.639
-HOBIE, WE'RE LEAVING.

23:00.204 --> 23:01.597
-OKAY.

23:01.728 --> 23:02.642
-NO NO NO NO NO. YOU
STAY HERE WITH KYLE.

23:02.772 --> 23:04.165
-BUT I WANNA GO WITH YOU.

23:04.295 --> 23:06.167
-I'LL CALL YOU IF
WE HAVE ANY NEWS.

23:06.297 --> 23:07.124
GO BACK TO SLEEP.

23:07.255 --> 23:08.430
OKAY?

23:08.561 --> 23:09.475
-OKAY.

23:11.085 --> 23:12.565
-EVERYTHING WILL BE OKAY.

23:12.695 --> 23:13.827
-OKAY.

23:17.396 --> 23:18.788
[SIGHING]

23:18.919 --> 23:20.703
-A GUY GOES TO A DOCTOR,

23:20.834 --> 23:23.967
SAYS, DOCTOR, MY NECK HURTS.

23:24.098 --> 23:26.579
DOCTOR SAYS, YOU EVER
HAD THIS PROBLEM BEFORE?

23:27.275 --> 23:28.581
MAN SAYS, YEAH!

23:28.711 --> 23:30.974
DOCTOR SAYS, WELL
YOU GOT IT AGAIN!

23:32.323 --> 23:33.760
THEN THE GUY GOES TO A DOCTOR,

23:34.325 --> 23:36.327
SAYS, DOCTOR, MY FOOT HURTS,

23:36.458 --> 23:37.981
WHAT SHOULD I DO FOR IT?

23:38.591 --> 23:39.461
DOCTOR SAYS,

23:40.462 --> 23:41.420
LIMP!

23:45.772 --> 23:46.990
BUZZY.

23:48.209 --> 23:50.124
BUZZY, LAND!

23:50.907 --> 23:51.952
LAND!

24:02.484 --> 24:04.660
-OKAY.

24:04.791 --> 24:06.793
THAT WAS MEL.
HE SAID THE LOCAL LIFEGUARDS
HAVEN'T SPOTTED ANYTHING.

24:14.888 --> 24:15.932
C.J.!

24:16.890 --> 24:18.369
I SEE SOMETHING!

24:18.500 --> 24:19.980
OVER THERE!

24:25.986 --> 24:27.335
IT'S THEM!

24:28.597 --> 24:31.034
BAYWATCH SCARAB TO SAN
DIEGO HEADQUARTERS.

24:31.165 --> 24:32.514
WE'VE GOT 'EM!

24:47.529 --> 24:50.706
[PANTING]

24:57.800 --> 25:00.847
[PANTING]

25:00.977 --> 25:04.328
[GRUNTING]

25:13.424 --> 25:14.948
HE'S GOT A PULSE.

25:15.078 --> 25:17.037
OH MY GOD, MITCH. WHAT HAPPENED?

25:17.167 --> 25:21.084
-[SIRENS BLARING]

25:26.612 --> 25:28.744
-[PANTING]

25:32.226 --> 25:34.663
-I KNEW RIGHT AWAY BUZZY
WAS HAVING A HEART ATTACK,

25:34.794 --> 25:37.753
SO I ANCHORED THE
BOAT THE BEST I COULD

25:37.884 --> 25:40.277
AND I WENT IN AFTER HIM.

25:40.408 --> 25:42.236
I STARTED SWIMMING BACK
WHEN ALL OF A SUDDEN

25:42.366 --> 25:43.803
THE WIND CATCHES THE SAIL

25:43.933 --> 25:45.761
AND IT'S LIKE I AM
WATCHING A MOVIE.

25:45.892 --> 25:48.590
THE BOAT IS SAILING
INTO THE SUNSET.

25:49.852 --> 25:51.462
WHAT'S THE STORY?

25:51.593 --> 25:54.117
-WELL BUZZY'S OFF
THE CRITICAL LIST.

25:54.248 --> 25:55.989
HE'S STILL IN INTENSIVE CARE

25:56.119 --> 25:57.556
BUT IT LOOKS LIKE
HE'LL PULL THROUGH.

25:57.686 --> 25:59.035
-ALL RIGHT! WAY TO GO, DAD!

25:59.949 --> 26:01.516
-THE DOCTOR'S
CALLING IT A MIRACLE.

26:02.648 --> 26:04.040
NICE WORK, BUCHANAN.

26:04.171 --> 26:05.868
-THANKS.

26:05.999 --> 26:07.740
-DID BUZZY EVER TALK ABOUT
HAVING A HEART CONDITION?

26:07.870 --> 26:09.263
-NO.

26:09.393 --> 26:11.004
NO, I HAD NO IDEA.

26:11.134 --> 26:12.527
-WELL HE MAY NOT HAVE, EITHER.

26:13.267 --> 26:14.355
SOMETIMES THERE'S
NO WAY OF KNOWING

26:14.485 --> 26:16.183
THAT AN ARTERY IS BLOCKED

26:16.313 --> 26:18.402
UNTIL THE BLOOD FLOW TO THE
HEART IS ACTUALLY CUT OFF.

26:19.186 --> 26:20.840
BUT IF YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE A HEART ATTACK,

26:20.970 --> 26:22.015
THE OCEAN'S THE
PLACE TO HAVE IT.

26:22.145 --> 26:23.582
-WHY IS THAT?

26:23.712 --> 26:25.888
-HYPOTHERMIA SLOWS
DOWN YOUR METABOLISM.

26:26.019 --> 26:27.890
YOUR CELLS NEED LESS OXYGEN.

26:28.021 --> 26:29.370
IT'S PROBABLY WHAT
KEPT BUZZY ALIVE.

26:29.500 --> 26:30.893
-NO, MITCH.

26:31.024 --> 26:33.374
YOU'RE WHAT KEPT BUZZY ALIVE.

26:42.035 --> 26:44.951
-LOUDSPEAKER: GOOD AFTERNOON,
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN!

26:46.126 --> 26:48.171
-MAYBE THEY'LL
GROW ON EACH OTHER.

26:48.302 --> 26:50.609
-IT USUALLY DOESN'T WORK
THAT WAY WITH THESE ANIMALS.

26:50.739 --> 26:52.654
THEY TEND TO REACT IMPULSIVELY.

26:52.785 --> 26:54.351
KIND OF LIKE LOVE
AT FIRST SIGHT.

26:55.483 --> 26:56.919
-WELL I CAN RELATE TO THAT.

26:59.705 --> 27:01.184
-IF THEY DON'T TAKE TO
EACH OTHER RIGHT AWAY,

27:01.315 --> 27:02.142
IT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

27:04.318 --> 27:05.319
-ROCKY,

27:06.059 --> 27:07.800
YOU'RE BLOWING IT.

27:08.452 --> 27:10.803
NO, THIS KIND OF OFFER
DOESN'T COME AROUND EVERY DAY.

27:12.021 --> 27:14.937
YOU NEED SOMEONE TO LOOK
AFTER YOU WHEN YOU'RE SMALL.

27:15.068 --> 27:17.287
TO LOVE YOU AND TEACH YOU HOW
TO GET AROUND IN THE WORLD.

27:20.943 --> 27:22.815
IT'S NOT AS EASY AS IT LOOKS.

27:23.554 --> 27:25.469
NOW GO ON, GIVE IT A TRY.

27:26.688 --> 27:27.950
WHAT HAVE YOU GOT TO LOSE?

27:43.487 --> 27:45.228
-LOOK AT THAT.

27:45.359 --> 27:46.882
THEY'RE BONDING.
I DON'T BELIEVE IT.

27:59.460 --> 28:00.374
[LAUGHING]

28:00.504 --> 28:01.592
HOW DID YOU DO THAT?

28:01.723 --> 28:03.246
YOU WANT TO TELL ME YOUR SECRET?

28:03.812 --> 28:05.466
-WELL, I'LL TELL
YOU ON ONE CONDITION.

28:06.510 --> 28:07.511
-WHAT'S THAT?

28:08.295 --> 28:09.775
-THAT YOU'LL HAVE
DINNER WITH ME TONIGHT.

28:10.514 --> 28:11.559
-OH, C.J.

28:12.429 --> 28:14.823
I GUESS THERE'S SOMETHING
I SHOULD HAVE TOLD YOU.

28:14.954 --> 28:17.739
I'VE BEEN SEEING SOMEONE
FOR QUITE SOME TIME NOW.

28:18.479 --> 28:20.089
WE'RE TALKING ABOUT
GETTING MARRIED AND...

28:21.830 --> 28:23.136
WELL, IT'S A
COMMITMENT I'VE MADE.

28:23.266 --> 28:24.441
-I UNDERSTAND.

28:24.572 --> 28:26.966
I-- JUST BAD TIMING.

28:27.836 --> 28:29.490
I'M SORRY. I DIDN'T MEAN
TO COME ON SO STRONG.

28:29.620 --> 28:31.100
-NO, THAT'S MY FAULT.

28:32.101 --> 28:33.581
I SHOULD'VE BEEN MORE
UP FRONT WITH YOU

28:33.712 --> 28:35.017
RIGHT FROM THE START.

28:38.194 --> 28:42.590
TRUTH IS, C.J., I COULD
EASILY FALL IN LOVE WITH YOU.

28:44.897 --> 28:46.420
-WELL, IN THAT CASE,

28:46.550 --> 28:47.595
I BETTER GET OUT OF HERE.

28:49.118 --> 28:50.816
DON'T WANNA MISS MY RIDE HOME.

28:52.513 --> 28:54.341
-WELL, I HOPE YOU'LL
COME BACK AND SEE US.

28:55.124 --> 28:57.692
YOU'RE ALWAYS WELCOME TO STOP BY
WHENEVER YOU'RE IN SAN DIEGO.

28:58.606 --> 29:00.260
-I JUST MIGHT TAKE
YOU UP ON THAT.

29:02.262 --> 29:03.306
BYE, ROCKY!

29:10.923 --> 29:12.185
YOU BE A GOOD BOY.

29:14.927 --> 29:15.971
-THANKS FOR ALL YOUR HELP.

29:21.455 --> 29:22.543
-BYE, KEITH.

29:34.990 --> 29:36.470
-IS THIS THE DRESS
YOU WERE THINKING OF?

29:36.600 --> 29:37.645
-YES.

29:39.125 --> 29:40.169
THANK YOU.

29:41.605 --> 29:43.042
YOU MAY GO, NOW.

30:09.329 --> 30:12.114
-[PHONE RINGING]

30:16.031 --> 30:17.337
-HELLO?

30:17.467 --> 30:18.686
-YOU HEARD ANYTHING
FROM OLD RUPERT?

30:19.469 --> 30:20.557
-SUMMER: NO.

30:21.428 --> 30:22.211
-WELL, HE MUST HAVE REALIZED

30:22.342 --> 30:23.125
THAT YOU WEREN'T DIANA.

30:23.778 --> 30:25.084
-YEAH, I GUESS SO.

30:26.563 --> 30:27.521
-MATT: WELL, YOU
SOUND DISAPPOINTED.

30:28.043 --> 30:29.828
-NO, OF COURSE I'M
NOT DISAPPOINTED.

30:31.307 --> 30:33.092
LISTEN, I'M GONNA FINISH PACKING

30:33.222 --> 30:35.094
AND I'LL MEET YOU DOWNSTAIRS
IN LIKE A HALF AN HOUR, OKAY?

30:35.224 --> 30:36.095
-OKAY.

30:50.718 --> 30:52.763
-WELL, HERE'S TO YOU, RUPERT.

30:52.894 --> 30:54.548
IT WAS SURE FUN WHILE IT LASTED.

30:55.897 --> 31:00.728
-[EERIE MUSIC]

31:03.339 --> 31:05.254
-RUPERT? IS THAT YOU?

31:12.348 --> 31:13.523
WE NEED TO TALK.

31:15.264 --> 31:18.354
-RUPERT: I LOVE YOU.

31:18.485 --> 31:20.879
-NO, RUPERT, I SAID TALK.

31:24.970 --> 31:27.886
RUPERT, PLEASE DON'T
MAKE ME FEEL THIS WAY.

31:29.017 --> 31:30.758
-RUPERT: I LOVE YOU.

31:31.715 --> 31:35.328
-NO, RUPERT, I'M NOT
THE ONE THAT YOU LOVE.

31:38.331 --> 31:39.941
-STEPHANIE!

31:40.072 --> 31:42.422
AH, I WAS HOPING I'D CATCH YOU
BEFORE YOU CHECKED OUT.

31:42.552 --> 31:43.423
WE DID IT.

31:43.553 --> 31:44.424
WE GET THE SCARAB.

31:44.554 --> 31:46.121
-CONGRATULATIONS!

31:46.252 --> 31:47.906
-AND THE WAVERUNNERS, THE
VOTE WAS FOUR TO THREE.

31:48.036 --> 31:49.733
-OH!
-YOU PUT US OVER THE TOP.

31:49.864 --> 31:51.300
-GLAD TO BE OF
SERVICE. [LAUGHING]

31:51.431 --> 31:52.911
-SO HOW'S MITCH?

31:53.041 --> 31:53.955
-OH, HE'S GONNA BE
RELEASED FROM THE HOSPITAL

31:54.086 --> 31:55.130
THIS AFTERNOON.

31:55.261 --> 31:56.349
-AND WHAT ABOUT HIS BROTHER?

31:56.479 --> 31:58.003
-BETTER THAN EXPECTED.

31:58.133 --> 31:59.743
THERE WAS A LITTLE DAMAGE
TO THE HEART BUT...

31:59.874 --> 32:01.397
I DON'T THINK IT'S
GONNA REQUIRE SURGERY.

32:03.660 --> 32:05.662
-I'M SORRY TO INTERRUPT,
BUT UM, HAVE YOU SEEN SUMMER?

32:05.793 --> 32:07.708
-NO, DID YOU CHECK HER ROOM?

32:07.838 --> 32:10.319
-SHE WASN'T THERE.
WE WERE SUPPOSED TO
MEET IN THE LOBBY.

32:10.450 --> 32:11.668
-WELL, THAT'S WHERE I'M GOING,
SO IF I SEE HER, I'LL TELL
HER YOU'RE LOOKING FOR HER.

32:11.799 --> 32:13.105
-OKAY.

32:14.367 --> 32:15.846
-WHATEVER HAPPENED
WITH HER AND THAT GHOST?

32:25.595 --> 32:27.075
-SUMMER!

32:30.209 --> 32:31.340
SUMMER!

32:40.784 --> 32:43.309
-RUPERT: COME TO ME.

32:44.397 --> 32:46.660
-I WILL, RUPERT, TRUST ME.

32:56.322 --> 32:58.759
-RUPERT: JUMP, DIANA.

33:08.116 --> 33:09.770
COME.

33:09.900 --> 33:11.902
-WE'LL BE TOGETHER. I PROMISE.

33:18.213 --> 33:19.432
-SUMMER!

33:19.562 --> 33:20.694
NO!

33:21.608 --> 33:23.566
SUMMER, GET DOWN!

33:24.915 --> 33:25.916
-RUPERT: DIANA.

33:26.047 --> 33:27.309
-DON'T LISTEN TO HIM, SUMMER.

33:27.440 --> 33:30.225
-RUPERT: COME TO ME.

33:31.748 --> 33:33.272
-HE DOESN'T LOVE YOU.

33:36.014 --> 33:37.624
I LOVE YOU.

33:49.418 --> 33:50.289
SUMMER!

33:50.419 --> 33:51.420
-SUMMER: MATT!

33:51.551 --> 33:52.856
-I GOT YOU.

33:53.379 --> 33:54.510
HOLD ON!

33:54.641 --> 33:55.424
[GRUNTING]

33:55.555 --> 33:56.469
TIGHTER.

33:56.599 --> 33:57.948
DON'T LET GO!

33:58.645 --> 33:59.863
[GRUNTING]

34:01.865 --> 34:04.042
[PANTING]

34:09.047 --> 34:10.873
[GASPING]

34:18.360 --> 34:19.579
HOLD ON!

34:19.708 --> 34:21.885
-[WHIMPERING]

34:27.108 --> 34:28.370
-RUPERT!

34:30.284 --> 34:31.417
LET THEM BE.

34:35.681 --> 34:37.510
I'LL GO WITH YOU NOW.

34:43.864 --> 34:46.562
[PANTING]

34:47.607 --> 34:50.175
[GRUNTING]

34:50.304 --> 34:52.742
-SUMMER: MATT, HELP ME!
I'M LOSING MY GRIP!

34:52.873 --> 34:54.875
[PANTING]

34:55.005 --> 34:56.877
[GRUNTING]

35:05.799 --> 35:08.715
[GROANING]

35:09.455 --> 35:10.499
-MATT: I GOT YOU.

35:10.630 --> 35:11.805
-SUMMER: OH, MATT!

35:11.935 --> 35:12.893
I THOUGHT I WAS GONNA FALL.

35:13.023 --> 35:14.764
-YOU'RE SAFE.

35:14.895 --> 35:16.505
-SUMMER: OH MATT,
YOU SAVED MY LIFE!
-IT'S OKAY.

35:16.636 --> 35:17.985
IT'S OVER.

35:18.725 --> 35:20.118
YOU'RE SAFE NOW.

35:23.817 --> 35:25.688
-SUMMER: HOW DID I GET HERE?

35:25.819 --> 35:27.951
-YOU DON'T REMEMBER ANYTHING?

35:29.039 --> 35:31.390
-NO, MY MIND'S A TOTAL BLANK.

35:32.347 --> 35:33.566
EXCEPT...

35:35.220 --> 35:36.917
-EXCEPT WHAT?

35:37.526 --> 35:39.267
-DID YOU SAY, "I LOVE YOU"?

35:41.443 --> 35:43.271
I LOVE YOU, TOO.

36:33.234 --> 36:34.148
-HOW YA DOIN'?

36:34.757 --> 36:36.194
-HOW DO I LOOK?

36:36.324 --> 36:38.065
-WELL, YOU LOOK A HELL
OF A LOT BETTER NOW

36:38.196 --> 36:39.197
THAN LAST TIME I SAW YOU.

36:41.329 --> 36:43.244
-HEY MAN, I OWE
YOU ONE BIG TIME.

36:44.027 --> 36:45.203
-YOU CAN SAY THAT AGAIN.

36:45.333 --> 36:47.030
-I OWE YOU ONE MAN, BIG TIME.

36:47.770 --> 36:48.641
-YOU-- YOU NEVER QUIT, DO YOU?

36:48.771 --> 36:50.208
YOU NEVER QUIT.

36:50.338 --> 36:52.558
-A PRIEST AND A RABBI
ARE FLYING TO NEW YORK,

36:52.688 --> 36:53.863
THE PLANE STARTS TO GO DOWN--

36:53.994 --> 36:54.864
-WAIT A MINUTE, WAIT A MINUTE.

36:54.995 --> 36:56.170
THIS IS SERIOUS.

36:58.085 --> 37:00.043
BUZZY, I TALKED TO KYLE.

37:01.697 --> 37:04.265
HE'S GONNA STAY WITH US 'TIL
YOU GET OUT OF THE HOSPITAL.

37:04.396 --> 37:06.006
AFTER THAT, IT'S UP TO YOU.

37:06.136 --> 37:07.442
-HEY, BRO.

37:09.270 --> 37:11.881
YOU KNOW WHEN WE WERE OUT THERE,
ALL I COULD THINK
ABOUT WAS MY SON.

37:13.492 --> 37:15.624
AND I PROMISED
MYSELF IF I SURVIVED,

37:16.669 --> 37:18.671
I'D NEVER LET HIM
OUT OF MY SIGHT, MAN.

37:18.801 --> 37:22.109
-WELL, THAT'S GOING A
LITTLE BIT TOO FAR,

37:22.240 --> 37:23.850
BUT THAT IS A STEP IN
THE RIGHT DIRECTION.

37:28.420 --> 37:30.291
HEY, YOU LITTLE GREMMIES.
COME ON IN HERE.

37:35.470 --> 37:36.689
HEY, MAN.

37:36.819 --> 37:38.473
MAN, I LOVE YOU.

37:38.604 --> 37:39.909
-I LOVE YOU TOO, DAD.

37:42.651 --> 37:44.436
-WELL NOW HEY, YOU PROMISE ME

37:44.566 --> 37:45.741
THAT THE NEXT TIME WE'RE
SUPPOSED TO GO SAILING,

37:45.872 --> 37:47.047
YOU WON'T RAT OUT ON ME?

37:47.569 --> 37:49.658
-I KNEW SOMEHOW YOU'D
PUT THIS ON ME, BUT--

37:49.789 --> 37:51.399
-WAIT A MINUTE,
NONE OF THIS WOULD'VE HAPPENED

37:51.530 --> 37:53.227
IF YOU GUYS HADN'T
DITCHED US, HUH?

37:53.358 --> 37:54.489
-YEAH, RIGHT!

37:54.620 --> 37:55.534
GIVE ME A BREAK!

37:55.664 --> 37:56.883
YOU'RE JUST SO FULL OF IT.

37:57.013 --> 37:58.885
-WILL YOU LIS--
LISTEN TO THIS KID.

37:59.015 --> 38:00.800
LISTEN TO THE WAY HE TALKS
TO THE OLD MAN, WILL YA?

38:00.930 --> 38:02.932
[LAUGHING]

38:03.063 --> 38:04.151
OH, COME HERE.

38:12.681 --> 38:14.683
-THERE YOU GO. THANKS A LOT.
-THANK YOU, SIR.

38:15.423 --> 38:17.382
-RADIO: AND THIS
JUST IN FROM LA JOLLA.

38:17.512 --> 38:18.818
A SAD NOTE,

38:18.948 --> 38:20.689
DIANA SUTHERLAND
HAS BEEN FOUND DEAD

38:20.820 --> 38:23.823
IN HER SEASIDE HOME,
APPARENTLY FROM NATURAL CAUSES.

38:24.432 --> 38:26.391
THE LEGENDARY SOCIALITE
HAD BEEN LINKED

38:26.521 --> 38:29.045
TO THE HAUNTING OF THE
HOTEL DEL CORONADO.

38:29.176 --> 38:31.613
ONCE AGAIN, DIANA
SUTHERLAND DEAD

38:31.744 --> 38:33.441
AT THE AGE OF 74.

38:35.574 --> 38:38.316
-WELL, I HOPE THEIR SOULS
ARE FINALLY TOGETHER.

38:40.100 --> 38:41.667
-IT'S AMAZING HOW
SHE STILL LOVED HIM

38:41.797 --> 38:43.233
AFTER ALL THESE YEARS.

38:43.364 --> 38:44.713
OLD RUPERT MUST HAVE
BEEN A HELL OF A GUY.

38:45.714 --> 38:48.238
-I'LL NEVER FORGET HIM.
THAT'S FOR SURE.

38:55.985 --> 38:58.292
-I THOUGHT YOU
WERE GONNA STAY HERE
AND LIVE HAPPILY EVER AFTER.

38:58.423 --> 38:59.293
WHAT HAPPENED?

38:59.815 --> 39:01.208
-I DON'T WANNA TALK ABOUT IT.

39:01.904 --> 39:03.384
-OKAY, WE WON'T TALK ABOUT IT.

39:05.560 --> 39:07.867
-[ENGINE REVVING]

39:11.871 --> 39:16.832
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

39:21.794 --> 39:26.842
-[ENDING THEME MUSIC]
